<h1>üêç Python Cheat Sheet (Beginner Level)</h1>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Python is a beginner-friendly programming language that is easy to read and understand.
        It is widely used by students to learn basic programming concepts and problem-solving skills.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Simple and readable syntax</li>
        <li>Uses indentation instead of braces</li>
        <li>Dynamically typed language</li>
        <li>Open-source and free to use</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Simple Syntax Examples</h2>

    <h3>Variables</h3>
    <pre>
x = 10
name = "Python"
    </pre>

    <h3>Data Types</h3>
    <pre>
a = 5
b = 2.5
c = "Hello"
    </pre>

    <h3>Conditional Statement</h3>
    <pre>
if a > 3:
    print("Greater than 3")
    </pre>

    <h3>Loop</h3>
    <pre>
for i in range(3):
    print(i)
    </pre>

    <h3>List</h3>
    <pre>
numbers = [1, 2, 3]
    </pre>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Real-Life or Business Use Case</h2>
    <p>
        In economics and business studies, Python is used to perform simple calculations,
        understand logical conditions, and work with basic data efficiently.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Advantages</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Very easy for beginners to learn</li>
        <li>Requires fewer lines of code</li>
        <li>Large community support</li>
        <li>Useful in academics and business fields</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Limitations</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Slower execution speed compared to some languages</li>
        <li>Not suitable for mobile app development</li>
        <li>High memory usage in some cases</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
        A Python cheat sheet acts as a quick reference guide for beginners.
        It helps students revise syntax easily and supports effective learning
        of programming fundamentals.
    </p>
</div>

